This paper discusses the governance and policy implications of artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of cs.AI. The paper also touches upon issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and privacy (cs.CR), which are important considerations in the development of AI. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for effective and anticipatory governance, which could involve machine learning (cs.LG) and social impact (cs.SI).
